    "recap_headline": "Oregon State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "CORVALLIS, Ore.\n\u2013 Oregon State's six-run seventh inning pushed the Beavers to a 7-2 win over Xavier Monday at Goss Stadium at Coleman Field, giving Oregon State the four-game sweep.\nTyler Inge\ndrove a two-run double to tie the game after Oregon State found itself entering the inning down 2-0.\nAdam Haight\nthen blooped in the game-winning, scored on a wild pitch, and then watched\nJacob Galloway\ndrive in the fifth run of the inning on a double to short center.\nBryce Hubbard\ncapped off Oregon State's (11-4 overall) scoring on a single to right.\nThe Beavers added on a seventh run in the eighth on another wild pitch and just like that the comeback was complete, ensuring Oregon State's sixth-consecutive win. Xavier, meanwhile, dropped to 5-11 on the year.\nAJ Hutcheson\ncame on in relief in the top of the seventh, and got out of a bases-loaded jam. He induced a 5-2 fielder's choice for out No. 2, then picked up a strikeout to close out the win. He eventually earned the win after the Beavers' come-from-behind victory.\nGalloway had two of the Beavers' six hits on the night.\nConnor Mendez\nstarted for the Beavers, and the first of five OSU pitchers worked four innings, scattering a hit and a run with five strikeouts. His lone blemish was a solo home run by Clay Burdette.\nBurdette put Xavier up 2-0 with a sixth-inning sacrifice fly.\nThe Beavers hit the road for an eight-game road trip that starts Friday in San Diego. The Beavers and Toreros get underway from Fowler Park at 6 p.m. PT. The game will air live on the Beaver Sports Network and ESPN+.\nFollow Us On Social\nFor more information on the Oregon State baseball team, follow the club's official X account at X.com/BeaverBaseball, by Facebook at Facebook.com/OregonStateBaseball, at BeaverBaseball.OSUBeavers.com on BlueSky or on Instagram at Instagram.com/BeaverBaseball.\nOUR MISSION\nOregon State Athletics strives to Build Excellent Authentic Visionary Student-Athletes (Go BEAVS)."
